location: "Hamilton, CA"
---
By the end of this course, students will be able to:

begin to understand the fundamental ways of thinking in Linguistics
use the tools of Linguistics to analyze human language behaviour in everyday life
explain how humans produce speech sounds
transcribe the sounds of Canadian English and other languages using the International Phonetic Alphabet
use data from a variety of languages to analyze how speech sounds are organized
